@NODE "mail_6" " Re: Absolute timing "
From: Thilo Köhler <koehlerthilo@...>
Date: 12-15-02 00:29:27
Subject: @{b}Re: Absolute timing@{ub}

Do it like this:

_________________________________Snip!
repeat:
starttime.l = Timer

.... Your code ...

waittime.l = Max(Min(starttime + 50 - Timer,50),0)
Delay_ waittime
Forever
_________________________________Snip!


This is safe if the Ticks overflow (which ocures about
after one year uptime ;-) and calls never delay_ with
negative value (i am not sure if this is matters).

BTW: This is no very accurate timing because you might
get errors about 1 VBlank and the VBlank is not the same
on every machine (50Hz Pal Amigas, 60HZ NTSC or
more on VGA Display). This will also cause trouble on Amithlon
where the VBlank is not constant when you cause IDCMP Events.

You could use the vvblank.inlcude from my homepage
(http://www.hd-rec.de/index.php?site=developer).
There is a "sync" mode that remembers the last call
of the vvblank_wait() command and is always
exact 1 second.

