On Sat, Dec 28, 2002 at 01:07:03AM +0200, Terje Maurset wrote:
> What I wish to do is, to make AmiBlitz set a comment om a target file:
> And I tried the following command:
> 
> --> SetComment_ "ram:test","BlitzComment"

That`s not how you should do it. Most amiga os api functions require a string pointer 
as argument(if they want a string), aka STRPTR. So do this:

string1$=ram:test"
string2$="BlitzComment"
SetComment_ &string1$,&string2$

The "&" gives the address of the string variable.

Regards

